---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Our Method" description="How we translate historical principles into modern, evidence-forward educational dossiers.">
  <section class="card" style="padding:22px">
    <div class="kicker">Our Method</div>
    <h1 class="h1">Historical principle → modern interpretation → formulation</h1>
    <p style="max-width:80ch;margin-top:10px;color:rgba(11,18,32,.84)">
      We work in a conservative, credibility-first way: translate historical preventive principles, interpret them in modern language, and summarize modern references using reputable sources.
    </p>

    <div class="hr"></div>

    <div class="grid cols-3">
      <div class="card" style="padding:16px">
        <div class="badge">1</div>
        <h3 class="h3" style="margin-top:10px">Historical excerpts</h3>
        <p class="small">Short excerpts (≤25 words) cited by page/section to preserve fidelity and context.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="padding:16px">
        <div class="badge">2</div>
        <h3 class="h3" style="margin-top:10px">Reputable references</h3>
        <p class="small">NIH ODS, NCCIH, WHO, EMA/HMPC, and PubMed-indexed reviews/meta-analyses.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="padding:16px">
        <div class="badge">3</div>
        <h3 class="h3" style="margin-top:10px">Compliant framing</h3>
        <p class="small">Structure/function language only. Educational content, not medical advice. No disease treatment claims.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hr"></div>
    <h2 class="h2">Quality mindset</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Identity testing (botanical ID)</li>
      <li>Heavy metals and microbial screening</li>
      <li>Pesticide residue screening (as applicable)</li>
      <li>Batch consistency and documentation</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
